article.headline: Texas St. 38, SE Louisiana 24
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Bradley George threw for 276 yards and two touchdowns to Cameron Luke to help Texas State beat Southeast Louisiana 38-24 on Saturday. Luke finished with 185 yards receiving on seven catches, as Texas State improve its all-time record to 12-0 against Southeastern Louisiana. The Bobcats (6-4, 3-2 Southland Conference) took a 14-7 lead in the first quarter on a 20-yard run by Stan Zwinggi, who finished with 82 yards rushing on 11 carries. Karrington Bush scored on a 4-yard run and Cameron Luke caught a 40-yard passing score from Bradley George to put Texas State ahead 28-7 in the opening quarter. Jasper Duckworth ran for a 6-yard touchdown, trimming the margin to 28-14 for the Lions (4-6, 1-4) in the first. But Karrington Bush rushed for a 4-yard score and Andrew Ireland made a 41-yard field goal, pushing the Bobcats lead to 28 points in the second to built enough cushion for the win. Karrington Bush had 18 carries for 91 yards and two touchdowns for Texas State. Brian Babin completed 21 of 35 passes for 228 yards for two touchdowns and three interceptions for Southeastern Louisiana. Jay Lucas ran for 100 yards on 12 carries.
